data.Name: Pressa
data.Bio: More times Pressa is a rapper from Toronto. Pressa is an associate/member of Wass Gang, a gang from Jane and Finch where Pressa grew up. He has been rapping in the Toronto underground scene for years but really picked up traction with his song Novacane which was produced by Murda Beats and also got co-signs from Drake, The Weekend and Coi Leray. The latter of the three collaborated with Pressa on the song Attachments which is Pressaâ€™s biggest song to date. Pressa has also worked with the likes of Lil Uzi Vert and Drake.
